                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00114A European War 1939/232: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-29T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 29, 1943—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 29—8:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Following telegram sent to the Embassy Madrid January 27, repeated for your
                    information:</p>
                <p>January 27, 10 p.m. Major Bernadoni has informed me from Melilla that he is
                    concerned about our soldiers at Tauima. He states that local feeling has
                    suddenly become very unfriendly and that their removal would obviate the
                    occurrence of incidents which may have serious consequences.</p>
                <p>I discussed this matter again with Castillo<note n="18" xml:id="d779fn18"
                        >Cristobal del Castillo, Spanish Consul General at Tangier.</note> in the
                    absence of the High Commissioner today and he promised to recommend at once to
                        Jordana<note n="19" xml:id="d779fn19">Gen. Francisco Gomez Jordana, Spanish
                        Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> that the men be sent at once to Spain
                    and that if this were not immediately possible they be sent near Tangier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
